                <head>307. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>From October 23 to 25, Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Harold
                        Macmillan</persName> and other British officials conferred in Washington
                    with President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, and other American officials
                    on several matters of mutual concern to their two countries. Documentation on
                    these meetings is scheduled for publication in volume XXVII. Among the matters
                    discussed at these meetings was the exchange of information on nuclear
                    weapons.</p>
            </div>
